children.subject:
What's your position for your discussion sections? How many open seats are there in these sections? Things may change dramatically once/if the 70% enrollment cap is lifted.

For example, if you're position 121, but discussion position 10, and your discussion has 13 open seats, you just need to wait it out. On the other hand, if you're position 10 for a full discussion section of 30 people, you're probably done for.
This is not information that you can see in the system. (You can kind of guess and what it is based on the number of people on the waitlist when you enrolled, but this will obviously change.)
How do you check discussion waitlist position?

history.content: In phase 1, I enrolled in CS 170 and 188, and tried to phase 2 just CS 161 but couldn't... so I waitlisted other CS upper div classes and currently in position 121 for CS 162 and 181 for CS 186. I am not planning on taking both at the same time but dropping one in the end because I don't want 4 upper div CS classes. So I was wondering what are the chances of getting into any of these two classes? Also, if I can't get into any of these two, what are some recommendations for 2nd year EECS student to take for the third class?
